14/06/2004
LISBON, Portugal -- Outsider Switzerland held Croatia to a goal-less draw in the two teams' opening game in the European Championship on Sunday (13 June). 
In the second half, Switzerland was forced to play 40 minutes with only 10 players, but Croatia failed to capitalise on the situation. 
Meanwhile, Bulgaria meets its first opponent, Sweden, late Monday. 
(AP, Reuters - 12/06/04)
